title: ITZY’s ICY gets 100 million views
text: Girl group ITZY’s music video for “ICY” broke 100 million views on YouTube over the past week, JYP Entertainment said on Saturday.“ITZY’s music video for ‘ICY’ passed 100 million views at 1:03 p.m. on Oct. 15,” the agency said.The news was likely held back as the entertainment industry mourned the untimely death of singer and actor Sulli, which was reported on Oct. 14.“ICY,” the second single released by the five-member rookie group came on July 29, following their hit debut track “Dalla Dalla.”“Both ‘Dalla Dalla’ and ‘ICY’ have passed 100 million views, proving their power as the monster rookie of the year,” JYP Entertainment said.ITZY made their debut this year in Feburary as the agency’s first girl group to come after Twice.ITZY is set to meet with their overseas fans through their first world showcase tour, which will begin on Nov. 2 at Jakarta.Their Asian tour will continue at Macau on Nov. 9, Taipei in Taiwan on Dec. 1, Manila on Dec. 8, Singapore on Dec. 13 and Bangkok on Dec. 21. They will then fly off to the United States and tour Los Angeles, Minneapolis, Houston, Washington and New York City.By Yoon So-yeon
